  <summary date="2021-04-29T15:04:36Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Stopping Overdoses of Fentanyl Analogues Act

This bill adds five fentanyl analogues and the entire category of fentanyl-related substances to schedule I of the Controlled Substances Act. A schedule I controlled substance is a drug, substance, or chemical that has a high potential for abuse; has no currently accepted medical value; and is subject to regulatory controls and administrative, civil, and criminal penalties under the Controlled Substances Act.</summary>
